node.text:
•
*TRIGGER WARNING* 

This video portrays the current unspoken state of the dance industry. Abuse comes in all shapes & forms. It can happen to anyone & can come from the most unexpected place/people. The cruel reality is that fear, judgement, and lack of support silences survivors harmed by those who are protected by social status and wealth. Leaving behind what has become an emergency within our community. It is time to begin the process for change. To protect all ages through not only raising awareness, but through education & action. To stand with survivors & hold abusers accountable. And most importantly - preventing the cycle.

Thank you to my sisters @macimontess @abbymel_ @malloryjul for this life changing moment together. I love you from the bottom of my soul. This moment will be tattooed on my heart for the rest of my life. 

Thank you @rudeboydonovan for saving my life.

Thank you to every single person in that room. You already know.

Thank you @billieeilish @finneas for using your power for GOOD. I love you & am so inspired by you. Thank you.

#YourPower #billieeilish

node.text:
•
A year ago today my angel was born & my life changed forever. When I tell you this little baby saved us - he came to us in 2020 & turned our worst year into the happiest year of our lives. I don’t remember what my life looked like before he was in it - and I never want to. There’s nothing I look forward to more than waking up each morning to his warm hugs, kisses, & loving beady eyes staring at me to feed him breakfast. I’m so thankful for every waking moment we share together & I cherish you to the deepest parts of my being. You are my dream come true. My best friend. My everything. And my entire universe. Thank you for showing me Daddy & Rudez the greatest love❤️ There’s nothing we wouldn’t do for you my sweet, Dunkin. You are tattooed on my heart for life & I will love you til the end of time. Happy 1st Birthday, my angel boy. #Dunkins1stBirthday #Ilovemyfurrbaby #doglover #dogbirthday #dogmom #dogdad

node.text: This morning I received the devastating news that my teacher, mentor, colleague & friend had passed away. Gregg Russell - you are one of the best people I have ever met in my entire life. From your infectious smile, to your incredible humor & undeniable talent. Your passion for human beings is what truly set you apart from the rest. A living legend. A loving husband & father. And an incredible friend to all. That I was so lucky to have. Thank you for all the life lessons. Thank you for being there for me whenever I needed guidance. Thank you for always being a listening ear. Thank you for all your incredible wisdom & advice whenever I felt lost. Thank you for always being a light in my life & making me laugh whenever I needed it. And lastly, for reminding me that being a good person & seeing the positive in things is what’s most important. My life changed the moment I got to teach alongside you at @artistssimplyhuman - never in a million years did i ever think I would have that honor. The greatest years of my life was being able to travel with you & my beautiful ASH FAM whom I love so dearly. The weekends will never be the same. And the dance community will never be the same. Thank you for paving the way for all of us to leave our dreams to the fullest with a smile on our faces. Today I am shattered. I will miss you every single day. And I will never forget the moments I was so honored to share with you. I love you, Gregg. We will dance together again, soon. Rest In Peace, Legend.

Thank you @ktla5news @kimberlychengtv for hearing us. Thank you for giving us this platform to expose the horrible things that happen & have been happening in our dance community for a very long time. Enough is enough. Silence is guilt. Silence is betrayal. Silence to cover up sexual abuse is SCARY. Not holding up a sign & standing up for what’s right. Saying “Maybe it happened, maybe it didn’t” from the owner of Temecula Dance Company is what is SCARY. Not standing up for the kids while practicing your constitutional rights to protest. Thank you to every single person who marched with @cierralauren & I last night. Your bravery is inspiring & we will continue to stand up for what’s right until we get the REAL TRUTH. WE WANT THE TRUTH. NO MORE ABUSE.

This was the best experience getting to know HARLEY. I wanted to know what it was like being in that cage without the love of her life (joker) after getting abducted by the government. Experiencing uncertainty & abuse. While also strategizing her next move because she’s the biggest bad ass on the planet. And the hottest. I had to have the most confidence while channeling my inner psycho. Thank you @circomisscharmionlafort for training me in silks for this project. All the motion sickness was worth it LOL. Thank you @vinnybalbo for training @nickfpauley & I in stunt work. It was so fun to dive into something different! What was your favorite part of the video?

node.text:
•
•

Last year around this time I saw the movie Joker - and it changed me forever. It inspired me to dive into more characters & develop a new passion for acting. Committing to a role is something that I can’t describe. It’s a ride that is so freeing yet filled with so much pressure. Last year was JOKER. This year is HARLEY. And I had so much fun with her. Thank you @nickfpauley for letting me play with you & for being the best person to get dirty with. You are such a superstar & I loved sharing this moment with you. Thank you @rudeboydonovan for directing this & helping me nail this character the best way I can. From driving me to silks lessons downtown & watching Scuicide Squad with me over & over again. Thank you for always helping me take things to the next level. Thank you @vinnybalbo for collaborating with me on this video & for training us in stunt work! You inspire me & push me! Thank you for choreographing our fight  scene! Thank you @directedbyjon for producing & helping us every step of the way on set. Your support means the world. Thank you @derrikadenisee @samuel.rayy & @alex_ayon for helping bring @nickfpauley and I to life with your magic! My Hair/Makeup/Wardobe team is EVERYTHING🖤 I hope everyone is enjoying Spooky Season! Thank you for watching & let me know what you think in the comments 🥰🃏🖤. @margotrobbie @davidayermovies cathyyan

node.text:
‼️FREE BRITNEY‼️

Class last night was INSANE🔥We danced for our LIVES!! I can’t even put into words how inspiring it was. The amount of passion & undeniable talent that exists in my classroom is unmatched! My students are the shit! Thank you to every single dancer that steps into my class every week & to all the new comers! It is an honor to be part of your lives & dance training! 

Give it up for my incredible assistants @tomo.takagii @christopheraguirree @dannyinestroza_ @jakegonzalesx 🔥

Choreo assistants : @scotticus96 @littleredxoxo 🔥❤️

Captured by @rudeboydonovan 🥰🎥🔥

Living LEGEND 👑 : @britneyspears - this is dedicated to you. We love you & we will continue to dance/fight for your FREEDOM. FREE BRITNEY!!!!!

#britneyspears #jojogomez #jojogomezchoreography

Dancers : @caitjoyho @annasantucci @bfongg @bailey_swift_ @jojogomezxo
